occurrenceRemarks: One of my big takeaways from field botany was the idea of succession and up here in Pine Flat it seems like one thing that is missing is a younger generations of the Ponderosa. I found this young tree here and decided to study it for CAPPS as a way to learn how the young Ponderosas are doing against the legions of knobcone and madrone that have come up around them. Even at this age there is no sign of pollen or cones, and so I wonder how it can compete with the trees around it who are already putting energy into reproduction.
